chunks.html_content: You must tell DVLA if you have seizures or epilepsy that cause déjà vu.
chunks.plain_content:
Déjà vu and driving
You must tell DVLA  if you have seizures or epilepsy that cause déjà vu.

chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.
chunks.plain_content:
Déjà vu and driving
You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.

chunks.html_content:
Talk to your doctor if you’re not sure if your déjà vu is related to seizures or epilepsy.

You only need to tell DVLA if your déjà vu is related to seizures or epilepsy. Fill in form FEP1 and send it to DVLA. The address is on the form.
